<div class="row featurette">
  <div class="col-md-12">
    <h2 class="featurette-heading">MindMup For Google Hangouts<span class="text-muted">&nbsp;online collaboration for creative people</span></h2>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <p class="lead">
    Online mind mapping tools so far focused on mapping features first, then
    built collaboration on top of that. The result was clunky and severely
    limited. People can work on a map simultaneously in almost any good mind
    mapping tool now, but conversation part is far below what our users expect.
    Chat systems are non existing or severely limited, there is no way to see
    collaborators faces or talk to them directly. For effective collaboration,
    groups had had to set up a separate video or audio channel using Skype or
    Hangouts. Synchronising participants across two different channels, setting
    up resource permissions and managing presence just becomes a headache.
    Jumping out of the mind map to a screen share to discuss a presentation is
    a hassle. No more! Instead of building collaboration on top of a mind
    mapping tool, MindMup for Hangouts puts mind mapping capabilities into one
    of the best collaboration systems out there!
    </p>
    <p class="lead">
    MindMup for Hangouts is trivially easy to get stared with. It brings all
    the goodness of MindMup, and removes all the hassle associated with
    managing collaboration over two different channels. Lightning-fast idea
    capture on keyboard? Check! See what your collaborators are doing? Check!
    Shift-space to set colours? Check! See people's faces as you discuss ideas? Check!
    Global access? Check! Waste time setting up privileges and document
    sharing? Of course not, it's done for you. Jump out to a screen share or a
    presentation? Just click on another tab in Hangouts!
    </p>
  </div>
