<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <h2>High-bandwidth brainstorming and idea review</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <p>
    Great collaboration needs more than just concurrent updates. To really benefit from a group mind-mapping session, people
    need to know what everyone else is thinking as well. With MindMup for Hangouts, we're coming as close to a physical presence as possible,
    by allowing you to hear and see collaborators, but also enssuring that you know what everyone else is doing around the map.
    </p>    
    <p>
    As people are moving around the map, you can see their profile photos move and follow their thoughts. When your colleagues
    add new ideas or update map nodes, you'll get a quick overview with pop-up speech bubbles. This ambiental information makes
    groupwork much more powerful than just remote simultaneous document editing. 
    <p>
    <p>
    MindMup for Hangouts uses the same mind mapping canvas as the main MindMup app, but simplified to fit in with the high-bandwidth
    communication provided by Hangouts. We removed all the noise so you can focus on your ideas, not on toolbars and menus. 
    Use powerful keyboard shortcuts
    to capture ideas quickly, or access common node operations from the convenient spider menu in the top-right corner. 
    </p>
  </div>
